And it's not just me who's experienced this.
I know that I am more fortunate than any of my colleagues, because the comments I receive are usually political.
I know how professional and targeted these colleagues are when they encounter a sea of discriminatory and racist comments every day, but never let themselves be caked.
One of the most disappointing aspects of this political era is how gross discrimination has become normalized.
Jeremy Corbyn said last week that the Labour Party should promote a culture of tolerance.
The truth is that we are no longer such a party that is open to everyone, and every mistrust proposal and every change of the electoral rules will narrow the party down.
I have received a lot of advice over the past two years where I am encouraged to keep my head low and not raise my voice so much, because it will “make everything better.”
That’s not why I was involved in politics.
Ever since I joined Labour 32 years ago as a school student, provoked by Thatcher’s government neglect that had led to my classroom at the public school I attended being literally fallacious, I have fought for better public services for those who need them most, both as local councillor and government minister.
I have never hidden my political views, even in previous elections.
No one in Nottingham East can in any way have misunderstood my political views or disagreements with the current leadership.
To those who tabled the proposal on Friday, I would just say that as the country is racing our way towards a Brexit that will harm individuals, businesses and public services, I cannot grasp and understand the desire to waste my time and effort on my loyalty to the Labour leader.
But the message I really want to convey is not to Nottingham Momentum – it’s to those I represent, whether they’re Labour members or not: I’m proud to serve you, and I promise that no threat of dismissal or political uncompromisingness will stop me from doing what I think best suits your interests.
Chris Leslie is the Member of Parliament for Nottingham East
